upstream: https://github.com/rcaloras/bash-preexec
commit:   a220343bf206372d4b90275eb30866c409f22f79
date:     2026-04-08
audit:    docs/decisions.md D016 (2026-04-11)

Pinned commit is 23 commits ahead of latest tag 0.6.0. Post-tag commits are
bugfixes authored mostly by akinomyoga (ble.sh maintainer) — bash-5.3 PS0/funsub
path, PROMPT_COMMAND sanitization, login-shell first-preexec fix #180. These
directly improve ble.sh + bash-preexec compat, so newer-than-tag is correct here.

Audit findings: 2 evals (both parse bash's own `trap -p DEBUG` output — safe),
DEBUG trap recursion guarded, no temp files, no network, no base64.
Caveat: __bp_adjust_histcontrol rewrites HISTCONTROL=ignorespace → ignoredups
and exports it, so ' export SECRET=…' (leading-space) becomes visible to
preexec hooks (notably Atuin) and to history. See CLAUDE.md.

Upgrade workflow:
  1. git clone https://github.com/rcaloras/bash-preexec /tmp/bpx && cd /tmp/bpx
  2. git checkout <new-commit>
  3. re-run the audit agent
  4. cp bash-preexec.sh LICENSE.md /opt/arche/vendor/bash-preexec/
  5. update this .source with new commit hash + date
